\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 A low murmur ran through the small knot of Legion officers. Everyone in the room understood the significance of the orders. As the civil war ran its course through what had once been a united Federated Comm
onwealth, any facility capable of producing BattleMechs and their various vital components had become a primary target. War, they all knew, was as much a matter of logistics as it was a matter of strategy and tactics.}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 The Lyran Alliance had two major 'Mech
 production facilities. One of those, Coventry Metal Works on the planet of the same name, had already fallen to Victor Davion. The other was the sprawling, city-sized Defiance Industries factory complex on Hesperus II, and the smaller, though no less imp
ortant, Doering Electronics manufacturing installation also on that world. Though Victor had yet to threaten Hesperus directly, everyone knew the Alliance's remaining major war producer was at risk.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Hesperus II lay within the borders of the politically unst
able region of the Lyran Alliance known as the Isle of Skye. With the Alliance's attention focused elsewhere, the Skye Separatist faction had used the opportunity to initiate yet another rebellious bid for independence. Given the importance of Hesperus II
 to both the Alliance and the Skye rebels, the Archon was reinforcing the planet's defenses by reassigning the Gray Death Legion.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "We're going to have to get the Legion together in one tearing hurry," Lori continued as the low rumble of commentary subsided.
 "We're to ship out in five days, and we'll make all haste for Hesperus. When we get there, we'll move into the base at Maria's Elegy and aid in the defense of the planet."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
