ic binoculars that she put to her eyes. Touching a control on the device's housing, she set the viewers to four power and scanned the valley. Aside from the occasional scrubby bush swaying in the gentle breeze, there wasn't much movement. Swinging to her 
l
eft and kicking up the magnification, Lori examined the pale linear structure. From a distance of four kilometers, according to the binoculars' range-finder function, the details of the high-speed maglev rail line were easy to pick out. She could easily s
ee the black line of the "rails" along which the train ran.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
