The sound of running feet echoed in the corridor beyond Lori's office. She looked up from the hardcopy report she'd been reading just in time to see her door burst open. Mick Cornwell, her orderly, stood framed in the portal.}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Colonel, a report from the comm center. They just picked up one helluva big IR flare." Cornwell paused to catch his breath. "This time, it's the real thing. They figure at least one big JumpShip, maybe more."}
{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Lori dropped the report. Whatever
 had downed the militia fighters was now unimportant. She brushed past the young man and headed for the building's front door. Outside, she found Davis McCall and Julio Vargas clambering into a hover jeep. She slid into the front passenger seat and slappe
d the driver on the shoulder.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Let's go. Comm center."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 The young man engaged the air-cushion vehicle's drive and sped off across the tarmac. Lori hung on grimly as the driver careened around the corner of a 'Mech bay, swerving to avoid hitting a parked Dril
lson heavy hover tank.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Take it easy, lad," McCall bellowed from the back seat.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Yer no in a race, an' there's no prize if ye don't get us there in one piece."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 The driver nodded and cut the jeep's speed slightly. Shortly after that, he brought the vehicle 
skidding to a halt. Lori jumped out, thankful to have solid ground beneath her feet again. Followed by her officers, she darted inside the port's main communications center and ran down a hallway.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Near the end of that corridor, two guards wearing the dark 
blue and green fatigues of a Lyran infantryman barred their way. Lori flashed her ID at them, eliciting a nod from the young, fresh-faced corporal who seemed to be in charge. As she passed inside the secure communications center control room, she noted th
e fear in the young man's eyes.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Thanks, Corporal," she said, pausing for a moment. "You're doing a good job."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Th . . . thank you, Colonel," the guard stammered. The aura of fear diminished, replaced by a nascent look of confidence.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Lori clapped him on the shoulder and stepped inside the darkened room. "General Ciampa?" she called above the low hum of the voices of the technicians gathered in the room.}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 A woman wearing the black-ribbed jumper and four I fetching bars of a Chief Warrant Officer came up to gre
et her. "The general's not here," she said. "I'm Chief Sellars, in charge of this station. General Ciampa is out of position. She's gone into town for the day. We're still trying to reach her."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Where is Colonel Brennan?" Lori asked, naming Ciampa's second-in-command.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 
"Don't know, Colonel," Sellars admitted. "I haven't seen her either. We've managed to contact General Zambos at his command center in Maldon. I told him what we've got. He's getting his troops ready for the invasion."}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Lori nodded. Zambos' duty
 station was all the way on thee other side of Hesperus II at Maldon, a huge mining installation owned by Defiance Industries. If the invaders stuck to the pattern, the mines would be left alone in favor of an attack on the main Defiance complex. But Lyra
n command had decided\emdash rightly so, in Lori's opinion\emdash that they could not rely on the Skye rebels to be predictable.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 So, Zambos' Thirty-sixth Lyran Guards had been moved to Maldon shortly after the Legion's arrival.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063 "Is}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446  this the invasion, Chief?" Lori asked.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
