Several hundred thousand kilometers away from the communication center control room at Maria's Elegy, on the bridge of the}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  Avalon-}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 class cruiser}{
\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  LAS Simon Davion,}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446  two other officers had just come to the same conclusion about the uninvited visitors to the Hesperus system.}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Leutnant-Kommodore Dieter Bern turned to his executive officer, with a look of grim determination. "Looks like this is it, Speer."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid13721370 "Ja}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 ,}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  Herr}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446  Kommodore," Kaptain Geron Speer said. "Long-range scans suggest both le
ading vessels are}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  Fox }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13721370 class}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446  corvettes."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Wonderful," Bern said under his breath. He had heard rumors that a number of the small, agile WarShips had been seized by their mutinous crews and turned over to the Skye rebels. Individually, the tough little
}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  Foxes}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446  would have been no match for the}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  Simon Davion.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 
 Together, the heavily armed corvettes would be able to dance around his cruiser and pick her apart. To make things worse, both rebel crews were all veteran spacers. "How long until we know for certain?"}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Fifteen minutes, sir. Maybe ten, if we really push the engines."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Bern considered his options. Although the}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  Simon Davion }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 
was the pinnacle of modern ship design, she was still mostly untested. She had performed admirably during her space trials and shakedown cru
ise. But even those rigorous days of testing and retesting had been conducted under peaceful conditions. They just could not compare to the stresses of combat.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "All right," he said at last. "Take us to flank speed. If we can reach the invaders before they 
reach Hesperus II, perhaps we can drive them off before they drop, or at least cut their numbers back somewhat." He looked over toward his communications off}{\f36\fs20\insrsid13721370 icer. "Comm, notify General Ci}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 ampa that we are moving to engage the invaders."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Kommodore, General 
Ciampa is not in command at Maria's Elegy," the young officer replied. "I have been advised that neither she nor Colonel Brennan is on the base. Command has been assumed by the most senior officer present, Colonel Lori Kalmar-Carlyle of the Gray Death Leg
ion."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "You mean Hesperus is in the hands of a mercenary?" Speer barked. "A mercenary who has invaded this planet herself once before?"}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "So it seems, Kaptain," Bern said, "but I suppose there are worse choices than the Gray Death Legion to defend Hesperus."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 
Even as he finished speaking, Bern felt the steel deck vibrate beneath his feet. A low thrum, more felt than heard, rang through the ship as the big maneuvering drives devoured an increased flow of fuel, converting the complex chemicals into flame, heat, 
and thrust. While it couldn't be said that the}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  Simon Davion}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446  surged ahead, the acceleration was nevertheless perceptible to a spacer's keen perception.}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Bern divided his attention between the ship's clock, the holographic image of the Hesperus system before him, and the constant stream of reports and requests coming his way.}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Kommodore, two of the vessels have begun moving toward us on an intercept course," a sensor tech reported.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "How long until contact?"}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "At the current rate of closure? Six minutes."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Very well. Sound General Quarters."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 No sooner had Bern given the order than a loud klaxon sounded throughout the ship. The fluorescent lighting strips set into the}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  Simon Davion's}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446  overhead flickered. When they came back on, the diffused white light had been replaced by an unearthly blue glow.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 
In theory, the blue lights were intended to help technicians and sensor operators read their instruments more easily. The eerie lighting had the additional effect of telling all aboard that the ship had gone to battle stations.}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Kommodore, the ship is cleared for action. All stations report manned and ready," Speer said crisply. "Shall I launch fighters?"}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Not yet, Kaptain. Let's allow them to get a bit closer."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "What do you intend to do, sir?"}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "All we can do is try to prevent the enemy from flanking us and concentrate our fire on the smaller target," Bern said.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
