al facility at the plant. Any serious cases can be airlifted to Maria's Elegy once they're more stable."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Thank you, Major. We're indebted to you."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Goree just smiled politely.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "One question, Major Goree," Brewer said sharply. "Why this change in attitude? 
Before, you were almost ready to take on the Legion, regardless of the fact that I'm the company CEO and Duke of Hesperus. Now, you're the poster boy for helpful cooperation."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "That was before the Legion proved its intentions." Goree's tone was flat and unemotional. "The difference is that now I know they can be counted on to fight in our corner. It's nothing more or less than that."
