\par }\pard \ql \fi284\li0\ri0\sa144\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\lisa60\pararsid13586446 {\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Repairs to the Gray Death Legion's BattleMechs were proceeding. Lori could s
ee that from her perch on the catwalk running around the outside of the huge 'Mech bay deep inside the DefHesp underground complex. Rebuilding the unit's morale would be much more difficult. More than half of the slots assigned to the Legion stood empty. 
In most of those cases, the vacant cubicles meant a vacant bunk in the Legion's barracks. The feeling that she had let the Legion down, and had failed Grayson's memory, writhed through her heart like a venomous snake.}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Stop it," she whispered angrily to herself. "You did your best and that's the most anyone, including Gray, could ever ask for."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Colonel, I hope I'm not disturbing you," someone said, coming up behind her.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Lori jumped at the voice intruding upon her gloomy thoughts. Feeling the flush of embarr
assment spread across her face and neck, she turned to see Gina Ciampa standing behind her, a steaming cup of coffee in each hand.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "I don't know how you take it," Ciampa said, handing}{\f36\fs20\insrsid10303482\charrsid13586446  o}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 ne of the cups to Lori. "I hope cream and sugar is all right."}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "That's fine, General." Lori smiled, taking the cup. If Ciampa noticed her embarrassment at being caught talking aloud to herself, she had the grace not to mention it. "Thank you."}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Ciampa took a sip a coffee. "That's something else. We've been calling each other 'General' and 'Colonel' ever since you got here. Don't you think it's about time you started calling me Gina, Lori?"}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Probably," Lori allowed. "Thank you, Gina."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Well, Lori, what now?"}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "I wish I knew," Lori said wearily. "The Legion is in bad shape. I've l
ost over half my strength, including all of my armored scouts. I've lost some key people, too. The warriors I have left are exhausted, dispirited . . . Hell, I'm feeling kind of demoralized myself."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 A long, bitter sigh escaped her. She shook her head in de
ep sadness. "I don't know how Grayson stood it all those years. I thought I felt the losses the same as he did. But now? Now I feel like I killed each one of them as surely as if I had pulled the trigger."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 

\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Ciampa snorted softly. "I know what you mean. Lori, please don't take this wrong, but I}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  do}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 
 know exactly how you feel. The last time you people were on Hesperus II, you killed and wounded an awful lot of my soldiers, destroyed an awful lot of my 'Mechs. I had to write 'those' letters. I always hate doing t
hat. And I blamed the Legion. In time, I got over it. I rationalized to myself that the Legion was just doing its job, following its own conscience.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Then, when I heard the Archon was sending the Gray Death to Hesperus, I discovered how angry I still was. 
There I was carrying around all that guilt for having lost my men in battle, only to be told that I had to accept the presence of the people who killed my troopers on the very world we'd fought to protect."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 

\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Ciampa stopped to take another gulp of her coffee
. Lori knew that having the Gray Death Legion posted to Hesperus must have been hard to take, not only for Ciampa, who hid it well, and for Zambos, who took no pains to conceal his feelings, but for the men under their command. How would she have felt if 
Katrina had posted the}{\f36\fs20\insrsid12538063  }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Fourth Skye Guards on Glengarry, given that unit's participation in the invasion of the Legion's land-hold during the rebellion of 3056?}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 She would have felt angry, would have felt betrayed by the Archon, to whom the Legion, in the per
son of Grayson Death Carlyle, had pledged loyalty. To be completely honest with herself, she'd probably have taken an attitude similar to that displayed by Peter Zambos.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "I had to make a decision," Ciampa said at last. "I had to decide if my devotion to th
e Archon was greater than my devotion to my own feelings. That always has to be the first consideration for a soldier, wouldn't you say? Loyalty to the greater cause. I know some say the first duty of a commander is to his or her troops. I think that by m
aintaining loyalty to the Alliance, and to the just causes it pursues, I am serving the best interests of my men."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Ciampa looked down at her mug, thinking for a moment. "They know I'm not about to throw away their lives in a hopeless fight, because, in the end, that harms the Alliance and dishonors the Archon."}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 She glanced up again, a strange light in her eyes. "I think, Colonel . . . Lori, you have a decision to make. I think you've already made it, but your mind hasn't notified the rest of you yet. Are you
 going to take this kick in the teeth, roll over, curl up, and die? Or are you going to pull your unit together\emdash for the good of your unit, if for no other reason\emdash stand up, dust yourself off, dig in your heels, and fight?"}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Lori regarded Gina Ciampa over the rim of her cup, masking her turbulent emotions behind a long pull at the steaming beverage.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Point taken, General," she said, intentionally using Ciampa's rank rather than her given name. "Of course we're going to dig in and fight. I suppose I should noti
fy myself first and then the rest of my warriors, eh?"}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "Those were the first two things I did when I decided to accord the Gray Death Legion the respect and consideration it deserved as one of the Archon's premier combat forces, rather than treating you li
ke a bunch of murdering cut-throats." Ciampa smiled to rob her last few words of any offense. "I made up my mind first, then I went about making up my soldiers' minds."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Lori nodded slowly, taking the other woman's words to heart. She looked out over the 'M
ech bay again. The empty berths still caused her heart to ache, as did the stack of "those letters" waiting on her desk, but the despair had faded to a dull throb. There was something else growing in its place, a new, refreshed determination. The Legion h
ad known defeat, but it had never been beaten.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "So, Lori, I'll ask you again, what now?"}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Lori saw an odd light of triumph in Ciampa's dark eyes, and she understood. This was a different kind of victory, one over an insidious inner enemy more dangerous than any enemy from without.}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 
"Well, I'd like to say the Skye Rangers are finished, but I know better than that," Lori said, pushing herself erect. "They still have enough 'Mechs onplanet to make up an effective combat force, and they still have that WarShip flo
ating around up there. That is one helluva force equalizer."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "I'd have to say it is a force}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  multiplier,"}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 
 Ciampa said. "They don't even have to bring her into direct action again. All they have to do is keep her onstation, and we have to assume they}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  are}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446  goi
ng to use her, either for fire support or to keep our DropShips and fighters on the ground."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Lori nodded. "Right. That will limit our ability to make rapid shifts in troop deployment while giving the Rangers the freedom to move their forces around with imp
unity. I don't really think they'll play it that way, but it might be a good idea to put General Zambos' men on the alert. We've given the rebels a couple of solid defeats here in the north. They might decide that cracking Defiance isn't worth the risk an
d move on to other, less heavily defended sites. I guess we'll have to send some of your troops back to Maria's Elegy, just in case the rebels try to take the spaceport."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Ciampa smiled. "Well, at least my people are getting in their cockpit time for the month."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 
"Then they're getting some good out of this mess," Lori said, a bit of humor creeping back into her tone. "The rest of us will fort up here until reinforcements arrive or until the Rangers make their next move. I'll have some of my armored infantry wo
rk with the few scouts I have left to keep track of the them. I don't want to lose contact with the bad guys again. This planet is too big to track them down without aerospace cover, and if we don't keep an eye on them, there are too many places the Range
rs could crop up to cause us trouble.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "I'd also propose we alternate sending out lance-strength patrols in maybe a three-kilometer radius sweep around the plant. That will give us some warning if the Separatists try it again."}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 Lori sat staring off into the 
middle distance for a time, as though it would let her see the entire Isle of Skye in a single glance. "The key to this rebellion is Defiance. The Separatists need 'Mechs to carry the thing through. If they don't get this factory, they'll have to try to b
uy them from someone, but I don't know if they've got either the money or the time to count on doing that.}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "As for Katrina Steiner, with Coventry in Victor's hands, Defiance is the Alliance's only major source of BattleMechs. I don't believe she can afford to lose this world.}{
\f36\fs20\insrsid15730155\charrsid13586446 
\par }{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446 "The Archon will}{\i\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid12538063  have}{\f36\fs20\insrsid15953901\charrsid13586446  to send us reinforcements, and soon."}{\f36\fs20\insrsid13586446 
